{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/organisations/office-of-the-parliamentary-counsel/about/recruitment","content_id":"e22e304e-44b2-4fa1-9b1c-e4d8a213ee59","description":"The Office of the Parliamentary Counsel is a group of government lawyers who specialise in drafting legislation. ","details":{"attachments":[],"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Office of the Parliamentary Counsel is headed by the <abbr title=\"The First Parliamentary Counsel oversees the Government in Parliament Group, which includes Parliamentary Counsel and the Business Managers in each House of Parliament. The Group works with teams across government to prepare and deliver the government’s legislative programme.\">First Parliamentary Counsel</abbr>. We are a team of some 50 lawyers and 10 support staff within the Civil Service. We draft government bills for introduction into Parliament and handle related Parliamentary business.</p>\n\n<p>Legislative drafting involves:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>analysis of a department’s legislative proposals</li>\n  <li>getting into the detail of how best the policy should be implemented in law</li>\n  <li>devising a suitable legislative structure</li>\n  <li>drafting the legislative provisions themselves</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/working-for-the-office-of-the-parliamentary-counsel\" class=\"govuk-link\">read some case studies</a> written by a few of our recent recruits. These case studies describe their background, experiences working for the office, and the areas they particularly enjoy.</p>\n\n</div>","change_history":[{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2018-10-22T14:39:25Z"}],"organisation":"9f80fe62-b229-4517-9e32-f560b5c518ce","tags":{"browse_pages":[]}},"document_type":"recruitment","first_published_at":"2018-10-22T15:39:26+01:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/office-of-the-parliamentary-counsel/about/recruitment","api_